---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Letter Frequency in Scrabble — How Often Each Tile Appears"
  description="Complete breakdown of letter frequency in Scrabble. Learn how many of each tile exists, which letters appear most often, and how frequency affects strategy and probability."
  keywords="scrabble letter frequency, tile frequency scrabble, how many tiles scrabble, letter distribution scrabble, scrabble tile count, most common scrabble letters"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Letter Frequency in Scrabble — How Often Each Tile Appears",
    "description": "Complete breakdown of letter frequency in Scrabble. Learn how many of each tile exists and how frequency affects strategy.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/letter-frequency-in-scrabble" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which letter appears most often in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The letter E appears most frequently with 12 tiles in the bag (12% of all tiles). After E, the next most common are A and I (9 tiles each), then O (8 tiles)." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many tiles are there in a Scrabble game?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A standard English Scrabble game contains exactly 100 tiles: 98 lettered tiles and 2 blank tiles. The distribution was designed by Alfred Butts based on frequency analysis of letters in English text." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why does letter frequency matter in Scrabble strategy?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Letter frequency directly affects tile tracking and probability calculations. Knowing that there are 12 E's but only 1 Z helps you estimate what tiles remain in the bag and make informed decisions about exchanges and rack management." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Statistics</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Letter Frequency in Scrabble: How Often Each Tile Appears</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>7 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        The 100 tiles in a Scrabble bag aren't distributed equally. Understanding exactly how many of each letter exists — and why — gives you a strategic edge in tile tracking, probability calculation, and rack management. Here's the complete frequency breakdown.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Complete Letter Distribution</h2>
      <p>Alfred Butts designed the original distribution by analyzing letter frequency in English text:</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Letter</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Count</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">% of Bag</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400 font-bold">E</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">12%</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400 font-bold">A, I</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">9 each</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9%</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400 font-bold">O</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8%</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400 font-bold">N, R, T</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">6 each</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6%</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400 font-bold">D, L, S, U</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">4 each</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">1-2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4%</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400 font-bold">G</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3%</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400 font-bold">B, C, F, H, M, P, V, W, Y</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">2 each</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">3-4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2%</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400 font-bold">J, K, Q, X, Z</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">1 each</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">5-10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1%</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400 font-bold">Blank</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">0</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2%</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Frequency Tiers</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">42%</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Vowels (inc. blanks)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">56%</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Consonants</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2%</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Blanks</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">68%</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">1-point tiles</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Strategic Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Over two-thirds of all tiles are worth just <span class="text-white font-medium">1 point</span>. This means bingo strategy (using common 1-point tiles for the 50-point bonus) is mathematically sound — you'll draw these tiles far more often than premium tiles.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">How Frequency Affects Strategy</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Tile tracking:</span> When you've seen 8 E's played, you know only 4 remain. This guides exchange decisions and defensive play.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Rack balance:</span> With 42 vowels vs 56 consonants, a 3-vowel/4-consonant rack is the natural equilibrium.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Singleton awareness:</span> J, K, Q, X, Z each have only 1 tile. Once played, they're gone forever. Plan carefully.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Key Takeaways</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🎯 Summary</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">E is king with <span class="text-white font-medium">12 tiles</span>, followed by A and I at 9 each. Over <span class="text-white font-medium">68%</span> of all tiles are worth 1 point. Track tile frequency during games to gain an information advantage and make better probability-based decisions.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/tile-distribution-explained" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Tile Distribution Explained</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-tile-strategy-letters-scoring" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Tile Strategy: Letters & Scoring</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/probability-based-play" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Probability-Based Play</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 See which words your tiles can make — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
